								</div>
								
								<div class="col-md-4">
									<h2>The Solution</h2>
									<p> Using the itunes API for searching podcasts, and the popular language PHP, we could provide podcast channels. Populating the SQL database, each user had their podcast channels saved for next time. Creating a playlist, user could save podcasts and listen to them in any order. With a bit of extra time, we created a podcast player to allow seeking and volume control. </p>
								</div>
								
								<div class="col-md-4">
									<h2>The Result</h2>
									<p> After a tough 24 hour marathon, the PodGenius web app was a success. <br>
										Next steps: Add the ability to filter using genres or categories, use a more efficient algorithmn to search itunes, and pre-buffer each podcast for performance. </p>
